title: Mike Braun
added: Braun voted to confirm [[Amy Coney Barrett Supreme Court nomination|Judge Amy Coney Barrett to the Supreme Court]] on October 26, following the death of Justice [[Ruth Bader Ginsburg]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Pinsker |first1=Adam |title=Braun Urges Senate Colleagues To Confirm Coney-Barrett |url=https://indianapublicmedia.org/news/braun-urges-senate-colleagues-to-confirm-coney-barrett.php |accessdate=November 13, 2020 |work=Indiana Public Media |date=October 20, 2020}}</ref> Braun supported his vote by saying that Barrett would be "...one of the best Supreme Court justices that weâ€™ve put on the bench in a long time; someone that is that humble and that smart and embedded in those Midwestern values."<ref>{{cite news |last1=Benbrook |first1=Julia |title=Indiana Senator Mike Braun reacts to confirmation of Justice Amy Coney Barrett |url=https://www.abc57.com/news/indiana-senator-mike-braun-reacts-to-confirmation-of-justice-amy-coney-barrett |accessdate=November 13, 2020 |work=[[WBND-LD]] |date=October 26, 2020}}</ref>
